1300:Iter-056 (this iteration) appends two thin foundational helpers about pairwise intersections of basic-open cover members. The Čech complex on a basic-open cover $\mathcal{U} = \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s$ at degree 1 indexes pairs $(i, j) \in s \times s$ and assigns the sheaf $F$ evaluated at the pairwise intersection $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,i \sqcap \mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,j$. By Mathlib's $\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_mul}$ ($X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(f \cdot g) = X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f \sqcap X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,g$), this intersection identifies with the basic open of the product $i.1 \cdot j.1 \in \Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$. Iter-056 packages this identification + the affine-membership transport into named project-local theorems so the iter-057+ Čech-evaluation argument can apply them directly via $\mathtt{simp}$ / $\mathtt{rw}$.
