1335:Iter-057 (this iteration) generalises iter-056's binary intersection helpers to the $n$-ary case: the intersection of $\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s\,a$ over a non-empty $\mathtt{Finset}\,s$. The Mathlib $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ at degree $n$ for a family $\mathcal U : \iota \to C$ assigns the value of the presheaf on the product of $\mathcal U(x_i)$ over $i : \mathtt{Fin}(n+1)$ for each $x : \mathtt{Fin}(n+1) \to \iota$. In the basic-open setting, this product (= intersection in $\mathtt{Opens}$) of $(n+1)$ basic-open cover members identifies with the basic open of the product of the $(n+1)$ generators in $\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$. Iter-057 packages this $n$-ary identification via the $\mathtt{Finset.inf'}$ shape (non-empty Finset; $\mathtt{Fin}(n+1)$-indexed iInf reduces to this via $\mathtt{Finset.univ}$) so iter-058+ Čech-evaluation arguments can apply it directly through induction on $\mathtt{Finset.cons}$.
