Generalises iter-056's pairwise (Theorems~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_eq_basicOpen_mul} and~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_inter_isAffineOpen}) to $n$-ary $\mathtt{Finset}$ indexing. Used by iter-058+ Čech evaluation at arbitrary degree: the Čech complex on a basic-open cover at degree $n$ has indexing $\mathtt{Fin}(n+1) \to s$ and assigns the sheaf evaluated on the $(n+1)$-fold intersection — converted to the $\mathtt{Finset.image}$ form (or directly via $\mathtt{Finset.univ}$ on $\mathtt{Fin}(n+1)$), this iter-057 lemma identifies the intersection with a single basic open of the finite product, ready for $\mathtt{IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}$ to land it as $\mathtt{Localization.Away}$.

\subsection{N-ary basic-open intersection inclusion (iter-058)}

Iter-058 (this iteration) appends a single thin foundational inclusion helper that downstream iter-059+ Koszul / Čech-evaluation arguments will need when constructing the morphism $V \to U$ for Mathlib's $\mathtt{IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}$. The Mathlib lemma signature is
\[
  (h_U : \IsAffineOpen\,U)\,(f : \Gamma(X, U))\,\{V : X.\mathtt{Opens}\}\,(i : V \to U)\,(\mathtt{hv} : V = X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f) \;\Longrightarrow\; \IsLocalization.\mathtt{Away}\,f\,\Gamma(X, V),
\]
which takes the inclusion morphism $i : V \to U$ as an explicit argument (used to install the $\Algebra\,\Gamma(X, U)\,\Gamma(X, V)$ instance for the conclusion type). To call this Mathlib lemma at $V := t.\mathtt{inf'}\,h\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s)$ in the iter-059+ Koszul argument, the inclusion $V \le U$ is needed up front; this is the iter-058 helper.

\textbf{Mathematical content}: chain iter-057's identification (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_eq_basicOpen_prod}) with Mathlib's $\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_le}\,(X.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f \le U)$ via Lean's term-mode $\triangleright$ rewrite. Total scaffolding cost: one three-line term-mode body.

\textbf{Why now}: keeps the iter-053 $\to$ iter-058 thin-scaffolding chain unbroken (one strategic helper per iteration, ${\le} 50$ LOC, kernel-only). After iter-058 lands, the iter-059+ substantive Koszul branch can directly invoke $h_U.\mathtt{isLocalization\_of\_eq\_basicOpen}\,(\prod_{i \in t} i.1)\,(\mathtt{homOfLE}\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_le}\,\ldots))\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_eq\_basicOpen\_prod}\,\ldots)$ without inlining the inclusion proof at every call site.

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[$N$-ary basic-open intersection $\le U$, iter-058]
  \label{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_le}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.basicOpenCover_finset_inf'_le}
  \uses{def:Scheme_basicOpenCover, thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_eq_basicOpen_prod}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $U$ an open of $C.\mathtt{left}$, $s \subseteq \Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$, $t : \mathtt{Finset}\,s$, and $h : t.\mathtt{Nonempty}$. Then
  \[
    t.\mathtt{inf'}\,h\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s) \,\le\, U.
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}\leanok
  Term-mode chain of iter-057's identification (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_basicOpenCover_finset_inf_eq_basicOpen_prod}: $t.\mathtt{inf'}\,h\,(\mathtt{basicOpenCover}\,s) = C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,(\prod_{i \in t} i.1)$) with Mathlib's $\mathtt{Scheme.basicOpen\_le}\,(C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen}\,f \le U)$ via Lean's $\triangleright$ ($\mathtt{Eq.mpr}$) rewrite. Body: $\mathtt{basicOpenCover\_finset\_inf'\_eq\_basicOpen\_prod}\,s\,t\,h\,\triangleright\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{basicOpen\_le}\,\_$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-058 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$.
\end{proof}

